gtecore.machine.absolute_baryonic_perfec: Put §bQuark Releasing Catalyst§r into the input bus to operate.
Each recipe cycle, different combinations of two §bQuark Releasing Catalysts§r will correctly identify the §bIsolated Quarks§r and complete the recipe.
Consumes all §bCatalysts§r in the input slot every second, and for each quark catalyst consumed, an additional 144mB of quark gluon plasma is required.
If the last two inserted §bCatalysts§r are the correct combination, §bStable Baryonic Matter§r will be output immediately.
At the end of the recipe, all incorrectly inserted §bCatalysts§r will return to the output slot.
§a§oThe final stage of purification transcends subatomic particles, identifying the smallest possible defects within baryons.
§a§oBy correctly identifying the required Quark Releasing Catalysts, the device will activate the catalysts and stabilize off-kilter particles.
§a§oThis ultimately creates not just stable baryonic matter, but most importantly, absolutely purified water.

gtecore.machine.biochemical_extraction.t: The machine requires specific fluids as input during operation; otherwise, the recipe is interrupted

After continuous operation for 5 seconds, it needs to input 1B cloud seed concentrated once
After continuous operation for 15 seconds, it needs to input 1B fire water once
After continuous operation for 20 seconds, it needs to input 1B vapor of levity once
If the required fluids for continuous operation do not meet the requirements, the recipe is interrupted; nutrient distillation can be input simultaneously with other fluids
After 20 seconds, only the requirement for inputting nutrient distillation once per second needs to be completed, recipe output begins

gtecore.machine.clarifier_purification_u: After processing a certain amount of water, the filter block will become clogged. At this point, a large amount of air (1-8KB) and water (200-300B) is required for backflushing. During backflushing, a certain amount of waste will be output.

Base output probability is 70%, inputting a small amount of the same level purified water increases the chance by 15%, and higher levels increase by an additional 5% per level, reaching 100% at the maximum of 4 levels.
§a§oThe first step to obtaining purified water is to filter out macro contaminants using large physical filters.

§a§oAs through rapid sand filtration for primary water treatment, 85% of bacteria and almost all turbidity (including silt, fine sand, micro-organic matter, inorganic matter, and floating organisms etc. suspended particles and colloids) are removed.

gtecore.machine.extreme_temperature_fluc: Complete the heating cycle by first heating the §bWater§r to above §610000K§r and then cooling it to below §610K§r.
Initial temperature reset to §6298K§r at the start of the recipe.
For each completed heating cycle, success rate increases by §433%§r.
If the temperature reaches §612500K§r, the recipe will fail and output §bSupercritical Steam§r.
Consumes up to §610mB§r of §bHelium Plasma§r and §6100mB§r of §bLiquid Helium§r per second.
Each consumption of 1mB §bHelium Plasma§r raises the temperature by §680-120K§r.
Each consumption of 1mB §bLiquid Helium§r lowers the temperature by §64-6K§r.
§a§oThe fifth step of water purification evaporates complex organic polymers and extreme microorganisms that may resist simple acids, clarifiers, and filters.

§a§oUsing ultra-high pressure chambers combined with extreme temperature fluctuations allows the water to remain in a supercritical state while evaporating any remaining contaminants in preparation for filtering.

gtecore.machine.fission_reactor.fuel: Number of Fuel Components: %s, Adjacent Count: %s
The reactor gains a maximum parallelism equal to the number of fuel components before it runs
The reactor will heat up based on conditions during operation, heating value (K) per second = heat generated by recipe x (1 + number of adjacent fuel rods)
If the supply amount is n times the demand amount, a special overclocking will be executed, overclocking times = n

Consumes one demand amount of cooling liquid again, reducing the time by 1 second. If cooling liquid cannot be supplied, overclocking is interrupted. If progress reaches 100%, overclocking is interrupted and one demand amount of cooling liquid is consumed to reduce temperature by 1K
Using distilled water as cooling liquid will generate steam, amount generated: consumption x min(160, 160/(1.4^(373-temperature)))

Using sodium-potassium alloy as cooling liquid will produce hot sodium-potassium alloy, amount generated = consumption. If the temperature exceeds 825K, an equal amount of supercritical sodium-potassium alloy is produced
Recipes can be executed regardless of whether the reactor consumes cooling liquid
The temperature of the reactor will decrease by 1K every second after it stops working
If the temperature exceeds 1500K, the reactor will be damaged; if damage reaches 100%, the reactor will explode
Provide cooling liquid during operation and control the temperature based on different cooling liquid coefficients
Cooling liquid coefficients: Distilled Water: 800, Sodium-Potassium Alloy: 20
Reactor cooling has the following parameters:
Minimum cooling liquid demand and maximum cooling liquid supply
Minimum Demand = Recipe Generated Heat x Actual Parallelism x Current Temperature / 1500

When supply >= demand, cooling liquid consumption conditions are met, consume provided cooling liquid, consumption amount = demand x cooling liquid coefficient, and prevent the reactor from heating up
gtecore.machine.flocculation_purificatio: During operation, all §bPolymeric Aluminum Chloride§r in the input chamber will be consumed.
At the end of the recipe, for every consumed §6100000mB§r of §bPolymeric Aluminum Chloride§r, the success rate will be further increased by §410.0%§r.
If the total amount of liquid provided is not a multiple of §6100000mB§r, the following formula applies a success rate penalty:
§a§oThe third step of water purification uses a flocculent (in this case, Polymeric Aluminum Chloride) to remove microscopic contaminants,
§a§o such as dust, microplastics, and other pollutants, through flocculation that causes solution dispersed suspended particles to conglomerate into larger clumps for further filtering.

gtecore.machine.high_energy_laser_purifi: During operation, replace the §bLens§r in the lens chamber.
When the current §bLens§r needs to be replaced, the multi-block structure will output a signal through the §bLens§r indicator chamber.
§bLens§r replacement requests will occur at random intervals between §66§r and 12 seconds.
The lens must be replaced within 4 seconds of the signal output.
Each successful replacement followed by 4 seconds of operation increases the success rate by §410%§r.
The requirements for §bLens§r can be viewed in the GUI, in a fixed order.
§a§oThe sixth step of water purification is identifying any residual anions in the water, which may cause electrical failures in future wafer manufacturing.

§a§oBombarding the water with photons of different wavelengths transfers energy to the outer-layer electrons, causing them to detach from the atoms and through the water tank walls, ensuring the water is fully polarized.

gtecore.machine.ph_neutralization_purifi: The initial pH value of each cycle varies between §64.5§r to §69.5§r.
§a§oThus, appropriate neutralizers need to be used to balance the pH value of the water.
If the pH value is within the §67.0 pH§r's §6±0.05 pH§r range at the end of the cycle, the recipe will always succeed.
Otherwise, the recipe will always fail.
The machine can read the current pH value and output a redstone signal using a pH sensor.
Consumes all input of §bSodium Hydroxide§r and §bHydrochloric Acid§r every second.
Each consumed §bSodium Hydroxide Powder§r raises the pH value by §60.01§r.
Each consumed §610§rmB§bHydrochloric Acid§r lowers the pH value by §60.01§r.
§a§oThe fourth step of water purification is to neutralize the solution and adjust its pH value precisely to 7, making the solution inert with no hydrogen ion activity other than that of water.
§a§oAcids and bases in soil and geology can cause natural alkalinity variations in water, possibly leading to corrosion reactions with sensitive materials.

gtecore.machine.residual_decontaminant_d:
Current cycle requirements:
%s
§aPurified Water Level§r: §f7§r
To successfully complete the recipe, materials must be inputted as required.
12, 14: Seldenian precipitation process
Do not input anything.
0: Machine overload
In rare situations, the machine may overload and not output any control signals.
To prevent machine damage, input §610000mB§r§bLiquid Helium§r.
Any liquid not requested by the input signal will always cause the recipe to fail.
§a§oThe penultimate step of water purification, step seven, consists of a series of irregular complex processes,
§a§oaimed at removing any residues of decontaminants that may linger from the previous steps,
§a§obased on the materials detected in the water by the degasser, it will request various materials to complete the above processes.
At the operation start, the degassing control chamber will output a redstone signal, and the machine will consume all input materials every second.
The redstone signal corresponds to the demand.
1, 3, 5, 7, 9: Ozone aeration via §bInert Gases§r
§610000mB§r§bHelium§r / §68000mB§r§bNeon§r / §66000mB§r§bArgon§r / §64000mB§r§bKrypton§r / §62000mB§r§bXenon§r
2, 4, 6, 8, 10: Superconductive deionization
Needs input of 1000mB of liquid superconductors corresponding to IV, LuV, ZPM, UV, UHV.
11, 13, 15: Gravitational Differential Vacuum Extraction
Requires input of §62000mB§r§bLiquid Amprosiums§r.

gtecore.machine.supercomputing_center.to: Putting computers together to provide lots of computing power
The use of advanced cooling solutions enables it to output more computing power
The machine's computing power is affected by the Hashrate correction factor
Maximum output computing power = computing power of computing components * Hashrate correction factor
When level is 2 or 3, the hashrate correction factor will change
Every 10 ticks, the Hashrate correction factor will decrease by ((Hashrate correction factor - 0.4)^2/5000)*(0.8/log(Hashrate correction factor + 6)) but will not be less than 0.8
The thermal conductivity can be input through the thermal conductive agent tank to increase the computing power correction coefficient. The thermal conductivity will become invalid after use.
If you upgrade to level 4 at level 2, you cannot upgrade further. If you upgrade to level 16 at level 3, you cannot upgrade further.
The calculation power correction coefficients that can be improved by thermal conductivity multi-function phase change (MFPC) and cascade phase change MFPC (Cascade-MFPC) are
Inputting ice shards is an extremely inefficient method, each providing 0.0001
The machine has three levels, switched by placing items in the mainframe:
The structure blocks of each level of the machine need to match the machine level
Level 1: Slots are empty - HPCA series components can be placed
Tungsten Borosilicate Glass - Computer Casing - Computer Heat Vent
Level 2: Place biological host - can place NICH series components
Neutronium Borosilicate Glass - Biocomputer Casing - Phase Change Biocomputer Cooling Vents
Level 3: Place the Hyper-Causal Host - GWCA series components can be placed (with built-in bridge)
Taranium Borosilicate Glass - Graviton Computer Casing - Anti Entropy Computer Condensation Matrix

gtecore.machine.water_purification_plant: Processing unit controllers can be placed freely within a §632§r block radius.
Shift-right-click the processing unit controller with flash memory, then shift-right-click that controller to link.

Provide power to the linked processing §6unit controllers§r. This multi-block structure accepts laser chambers, default energy consumption = input water count x 2^(output purification water tier - 2).
Operates with a fixed processing cycle of §6120§r seconds.
All linked processing unit controllers follow this cycle; purified water output is the volume of input water x 0.9mB.
§a§oPollutants and ionic particles in water can cause significant defects during the precise processes of wafer and chip cutting and engraving.
§a§oIt is crucial to systematically purify the water through a series of increasingly precise and complex processes, and this multi-block structure is the core of the operation.
